e 17th century. By the 18th century, Latin American countries became massive producers, with Brazil eventually growing into the world's largest coffee producer.\nItalian Innovations: Italy fundamentally changed how coffee is made. Milanese engineer Luigi Bezzera invented the first espresso machine in 1901.\nModern Specialty Era: The 1960s and 1970s sparked a specialty coffee movement, with the founding of chains like Starbucks in Seattle in 1971, evolving into today's focus on fair-trade, artisanal, and single-origin roasts.\u00a0\nwww.portioli.it\n\u00a0+2\nHistory of coffee - NCA\n30 mar 2025 \u2014 9th Century: Innovation on the Ethiopian Plateau. According to legend, a goat herder named Kaldi was the first person who discover...\nAbout Coffee - National Coffee Association\nHistory of coffee - Wikipedia\nThe history of coffee spans many centuries. Wild coffee plants originated in Ethiopia, while the beverage itself has its roots in ...\nWikipedia\nThe history of Italian coffee - From its origins to today - Portioli\n15 mag 2026 \u2014 The origins of coffee date back to Kaffa region of Ethiopia, where the coffee plant is native. Legend has it that an Ethiopian she...\nwww.portioli.it\nMostra tutto\nMostra altro"
